3. Allocate array a:

   int *a = (int *)malloc(sizeof(int) * (len + 1));

   Initialize all elements to 0. But in the Python code, a is initialized to zeros. So in C, after allocation, we need to set all elements to 0. Since malloc doesn't initialize, we can use calloc instead. a = calloc(len +1, sizeof(int));

