The loop is for i in range(1, len(soz)), which for len(soz) being 3, i would be 1 and 2. So in C, the loop should run for i from 1 to len-1, exclusive. So i < len. Because in Python, range(a, b) is a <= i < b. So for range(1, len_soz), the loop runs for i=1,2,..., len_soz-1-1? Wait, no. Let me think. For example, if len_soz is 3, then range(1, len_soz) is 1, 2. So in C, the loop is for (i = 1; i < len_soz; i++). Because len_soz is 3, i goes up to 2. So yes. So:

